social_posts.post_text: Moved my shop over to another platform to sell all my leftover stock from a few years ago. Right now this is all I have, but I’m considering adding some new things to my shop in the near future…(??) Link is shown above, or can be accessed via my linktree or on my story :-)
Spent this month playing Pikmin Bloom (80%) and getting my fall festivities in (20%)

Postcard Painting 1/5: Patron Saint of Going To The Grocery At 10 AM On A Thursday Because You’re Out Of Eggs But You Might As Well Buy A Treat Too. This original along with 4 others will be dropped in my shop soon (patrons know the exact date and time!) #gouache #characterdesign

Postcard Painting 2/5. The Patron Saint of Creating In Your Space. This character, Dots, has become one of my very few recurring characters. They have become sort of a representation of creativity for me :-) #illustration #gouache #characterdesign

social_posts.post_text: Painted Postcard 3/5: Patron Saint of Perfect Balance. I originally drew this character in my sketchbook many months ago to make out clay and rope. I still hope to make it happen! #illustration #gouache #characterdesign

Postcard Painting 5/5: The Patron Saint of Play. This guy is another character I drew up a couple months ago but just really enjoyed the shape of his head and pointy cape! These postcards will all be for sale in my shop in a few days. (Patrons know what day and time of the drop!) ;-D #illustration #postcard #gouache #characterdesign #kidslitart
All five paintings are available now :-D I will be likely doing this every month if I have the time. Five paintings, once a month! #mixedmedia #nintendocore #illustration #gouache

New Tier! Check it out! If you like my video content this is the place to be. Also printables / digital downloads coming back as a reward from one of my old tiers :-] your support is very cool, thanks everyone.

Excited to share the cover and some interior snippets from Wildlife Crossings of Hope by Teddy Lynn Chichester, coming Summer 2024! This book is all about wildlife crossings and corridor projects helping creatures move freely and safely through the world. Anytime I get to draw animals I’m thrilled, and when I get to draw a salmon canon (!!) I’m even more delighted. 🦡🐂🦍🐢🐘🐜🐟 #stembooks #wildlifecrossing #animalbooks #nonfictionbooks #earthsciencebooks #bookillustration #animaldrawing
